    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-08-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="117"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2039.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-08-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 13, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    despatch of the 22d of July, No. 1409. It authorizes me to assume that you will
                    cheerfully comply with the joint resolution of Congress in regard to the dress
                    to be worn on state ceremonial occasions. I have not the least doubt that your
                    discretion will be a better guide for your proceedings in matters collateral
                    with that subject than any instructions which could be given by this
                    department.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
